basic Entity Framework Code-First console application** that creates a simple `Student` database and adds one student. This example uses **Entity Framework 6**, which is the most common for .NET Framework console apps.

### 2. Student Class

```csharp
using System;
using System.Data.Entity;

// The Student class represents a table in the database.
public class Student
{
    // Primary key property
    public int StudentId { get; set; }
    // Name property
    public string Name { get; set; }
}

// The context class manages the entity objects during runtime,
// including populating objects with data from a database, change tracking, and persisting data to the database.
public class SchoolContext : DbContext
{
    // The Students property will be mapped to a Students table in the database.
    public DbSet<Student> Students { get; set; }
}

class Program
{
    static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        // Create an instance of the context (database connection)
        using (var db = new SchoolContext())
        {
            // Create a new student object
            var student = new Student() { Name = "John Doe" };

            // Add the student to the Students DbSet
            db.Students.Add(student);

            // Save changes to the database (this will create the database if it doesn't exist)
            db.SaveChanges();

            // Display confirmation
            Console.WriteLine("Student added successfully!");
        }

        // Wait for user input before closing
        Console.ReadLine();
    }
}
```

---

### 3. App.config Example

Add this to your `App.config` file so EF knows where to create the database:

```xml
<configuration>
  <connectionStrings>
    <add name="SchoolContext"
         connectionString="Data Source=(localdb)\MSSQLLocalDB;Initial Catalog=CodeFirstStudentDb;Integrated Security=True;"
         providerName="System.Data.SqlClient" />
  </connectionStrings>
</configuration>
```

---

### 4. What Happens

- When you run the app, Entity Framework will create a new database called `CodeFirstStudentDb` (if it doesnâ€™t already exist).
- It will add a single student named "John Doe" to the `Students` table.

